Details on the map: Checkered is a scaled-down recreation of Port Angeles, Washington, carved into 25 zones. Attend Peninsula College, bust out of Clallam County Courthouse, hotwire Coast Guard's MH-65 Dolphin helicopters, freeze in the Strait of Juan de Fuca, hunt deer where Bigfoot roams, disappear into the Olympic Mountains, and run Highway 101 in an OBS or a Taco.

