8) Auntie Nani Mahoe : "Choose who you trust". Henry Jim leaves to Hawaii and his sister temporarily runs the Whispering Pines. She gets to know you closer. But Henry would tell his sister about your curse, he cares about her more, since he literally left to the city and abandoned Syl after discovering the curse. But also he let Syl stay and live in the attic, so they have a strained realtionship. So would Henry leave his sister alone with a killer? Doesn't make sense. Week 30

9) Dr. Elena Vance the campus psychologist. Latina, transferred from Seattle. Sharp, empathetic, young, extremely patient and calculating but appears friendly, impossible to lie to. Usually operates in a duo with dr... - he handles the group's skeptics/leader while she speaks to the crowd/the more vulnerable/easily influenced. The college mandates evaluation, Vance looks at your activity for the past 15 weeks and notices something wrong, leading to a series of further evaluations. Week 36

10) Vera Morales (WIP ???) Clallam County social worker (detective? sheriff? private investigator? scientist? military?) no patience for bullshit. She has read every police report, school file, and hospital record tied to "Reed St. Clair" and the Chichuru sightings. Vera is the convergence. She arrives because the system is broken — too many reports, too many contradictions. She introduces THE CHOICE. She offers a structured exit: turn yourself in, enter a diversion program, get therapy and housing. Or she warns you that prosecution is inevitable and she will be the one to process you. If you befriended everyone and kept crime low, she gets you into a residential treatment program. The final scene is not a shootout. It is you walking into a building with a window, not a cell. You chose to be human. Antagonist reward (Other routes): In the Void route, she becomes the final pursuer — the one person who will not stop hunting you because she sees you as a victim who needs saving, not a villain who needs killing. In the Engineer route, she accidentally triggers your most lethal trap and you must decide whether to let her die or disarm it. Week 38